  "title": "Project Site Engineer (Electrical / M&E) | Tampines | Up to $4,500 + AWS + Bonus",
  "description": "<p>📍 <strong>Location:</strong> Tampines<br />🕒 <strong>Working Hours:</strong> Monday – Friday, 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM<br />🎁 <strong>Benefits:</strong> 13th Month AWS, Annual Bonus, 14 Days Annual Leave</p><h3><strong>About the Company</strong></h3><p>Our client is a reputable <strong>construction and engineering firm</strong> headquartered in <strong>China</strong> and <strong>listed on NASDAQ</strong>. With established operations in Singapore, the company focuses on <strong>infrastructure development, M&E installation, and integrated engineering projects</strong>. They are now seeking a dedicated <strong>Project Site Engineer (Electrical / M&E)</strong> to join their expanding local team.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Conduct site inspections, maintain site diary, and record project progress.</li><li>Monitor work schedule, manpower deployment, and site coordination.</li><li>Oversee the use of construction materials and equipment on-site.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve technical or site-related issues.</li><li>Ensure safety, quality, and regulatory compliance are maintained.</li><li>Prepare progress reports and recommend corrective measures when necessary.</li><li>Support installation works such as cable trays, conduits, cabling, and equipment layout.</li><li>Assist the Project Manager in project execution and site supervision.</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Electrical Engineering, M&E, or a related discipline</strong>.</li><li>Minimum <strong>2 years of relevant site experience</strong> in M&E/ELV works.</li><li>Proficient in <strong>AutoCAD</strong> and <strong>Microsoft Office</strong> applications.</li><li>Familiar with Singapore <strong>construction laws, safety standards, and site procedures</strong>.</li><li>Strong coordination, communication, and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Bilingual in <strong>English and Mandarin</strong> to liaise with HQ.</li></ul><p>EA License No: 23C1703 </p><p>EA Personnel No: R1762582 </p><p>EA Personnel Name: Wong Choo Sian, Jabez</p>",
